To pie for 🥧 In case you need a last minute Thanksgiving dessert, or inspo for holiday baking, this gorgeous cranberry galette can be made in under an hour with nothing but fresh cranberries, premade pie crust and pantry staples. It’s the perfect mix of tart and sweet and looks oh so pretty on a festive table. Recipe below. 

Cranberry Galette

Crust:
1 refrigerate pie crust, thawed
1 Tbsp plain yogurt
1/4 tsp cinnamon

Filling
2 cups fresh cranberries
1/2 cup brown sugar
2 Tbsp white sugar
1 1/3 Tbsp cornstarch
1 tsp vanilla
pinch of salt

1. preheat oven to 375 degrees
2. combine all the filling ingredients, except the white sugar, in a bowl and mix well.
3. roll the pie dough into a 12-inch circle and place on a parchment paper lined baking sheet.
4. pour cranberry filling into the center of the dough, leaving a border about 2 1/2 inches.  Fold the outer edges of the dough over the filling.
5. Mix yogurt and cinnamon and brush onto folded over edges of the dough.
6.  Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
7.  Let cool, and sprinkle filling with white sugar just before serving.
